<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Common Durian Types</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #3f51b5;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 100%; /* Adjust to your preference */
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .durian-card {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column; /* Stack content vertically on small screens */
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .durian-img {
            flex: 0 0 auto; /* Let the image size determine its width */
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center; /* Center the image */
        }

        .durian-img img {
            max-width: 100%; /* Ensure images don't overflow the container */
            height: 200px; /* Fixed height for all images */
            width: auto; /* Allow width to adjust based on height */
        }

        .durian-info {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 10px;
        }

        h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        p {
            margin: 0;
            line-height: 1.4;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Common Durian Types</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="musangking.png" alt="Musang King Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Musang King (Mao Shan Wang)</h2>
                <p>Known for its rich and creamy flesh, Musang King is one of the most sought-after durian varieties. It
                    has a distinctive bittersweet taste and a strong aroma.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Add more durian cards here -->
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="d24.jpg" alt="D24 Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>D24</h2>
                <p>D24 durian is famous for its golden-yellow flesh and a balanced mix of sweetness and bitterness. It's often enjoyed for its creamy texture.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="blackthorn.jpg" alt="Black Thorn Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Black Thorn</h2>
                <p>This durian variety is known for its small size, distinctive dark purple husk, and creamy, bittersweet flesh.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="redprawn.jpg" alt="Red Prawn (Ang Hae) Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Red Prawn (Ang Hae)</h2>
                <p>Red Prawn durian has a reddish-orange hue and a sweet, custard-like taste. It's loved for its smooth and velvety texture.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="goldenphoenix.jpg" alt="Golden Phoenix (Jin Feng) Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Golden Phoenix (Jin Feng)</h2>
                <p>With a pale yellow flesh and a mild, nutty flavor, Golden Phoenix durian is appreciated for its unique taste and aroma.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="d101.jpg" alt="D101 Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>D101</h2>
                <p>D101 durian is favored for its mildly sweet and creamy taste. It's often described as having a subtle sweetness and a smooth texture.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="xo.jpg" alt="XO Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>XO</h2>
                <p>XO durian is aged longer, giving it a distinct taste and aroma. It has a stronger and more complex flavor profile with hints of alcohol-like notes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="horlor.jpg" alt="Hor Lor (Hei Law) Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Hor Lor (Hei Law)</h2>
                <p>Hor Lor durian is known for its elongated shape and a balance between sweetness and bitterness. It has a rich and creamy texture.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="greenbamboo.jpg" alt="Green Bamboo (Tekka) Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Green Bamboo (Tekka)</h2>
                <p>Green Bamboo durian has a pale green husk and a mild taste with hints of bitterness. It's often enjoyed for its refreshing flavor.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="monthong.webp" alt="Mornthong Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Mornthong</h2>
                <p>Mornthong durian is popular for its bright yellow flesh and a pleasant mix of sweetness and bitterness.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="Kanyao.webp" alt="Kanyao Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Kanyao</h2>
                <p>Kanyao durian is appreciated for its delicate and tender flesh, as well as its mild and sweet taste.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="durian-card">
            <div class="durian-img">
                <img src="Chanee.png" alt="Chanee Durian">
            </div>
            <div class="durian-info">
                <h2>Chanee</h2>
                <p>Chanee durian has a pale yellow flesh with a sweet and fragrant flavor. It's known for being one of the larger durian varieties.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
